1
00:01:35,759 --> 00:01:38,280
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,420 --> 00:01:41,280
[Episode 8]

3
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:42,560
What kind of perm

4
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,430
would you like, handsome?

5
00:01:43,430 --> 00:01:45,509
I want something...

6
00:01:45,509 --> 00:01:47,430
understated yet stylish—

7
00:01:47,430 --> 00:01:48,590
something fresh

8
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:51,070
yet striking.

9
00:01:51,789 --> 00:01:52,920
Sure, we can do that!

10
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:16,130
[Full scholarship admission
decision letter from a U.S. University]

11
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:16,720
Doesn't meet admission requirements.

12
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,760
I think I've got something in my eye.

13
00:02:58,760 --> 00:02:59,840
Don't touch it!

14
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:00,840
Let me see!

15
00:03:05,030 --> 00:03:06,360
There's nothing there.

16
00:03:06,430 --> 00:03:07,490
Do you feel better?

17
00:03:08,780 --> 00:03:12,850
♪ Watching your profile draw near,
I smile like a fool ♪

18
00:03:13,450 --> 00:03:17,120
♪ Every word you said, like a melody,
sprouts in my heart ♪

19
00:03:17,930 --> 00:03:21,950
♪ The sparks between us
burn bright within the notes ♪

20
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:22,710
I-I'll go put in some eye drops.

21
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:26,250
♪ How I long for an answer from you ♪

22
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:23,710
That should help.

23
00:03:26,579 --> 00:03:28,600
♪ My heart won't stop its racing beat ♪

24
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:31,450
♪ The sweetness when our eyes meet ♪

25
00:03:31,940 --> 00:03:35,610
♪ Each time we meet,
it's as if the dream goes on ♪

26
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:33,680
Catch it!

27
00:03:36,010 --> 00:03:38,200
♪ How I wish to tell you ♪

28
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:37,430
Be careful!

29
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:38,870
Be careful!

30
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,579
♪ It's not a coincidence or a miracle ♪

31
00:03:42,650 --> 00:03:45,410
♪ It's destiny ♪

32
00:03:44,870 --> 00:03:45,630
Time's almost up.

33
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:47,470
♪ Sharing my earbuds with you ♪

34
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:46,310
We should head back to class.

35
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:47,400
Mr. Bu, class hasn't even started yet.

36
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:47,870
Let us play a bit longer.

37
00:03:47,490 --> 00:03:49,630
♪ Connecting you to my heartbeat ♪

38
00:03:47,890 --> 00:03:48,590
Just a bit.

39
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:49,690
Alright, alright.

40
00:03:49,690 --> 00:03:51,740
♪ Scrolling up and down the playlist ♪

41
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:50,520
Be careful.

42
00:03:50,550 --> 00:03:51,110
Okay.

43
00:03:51,829 --> 00:03:55,210
♪ Disrupting the rhythm of my breath ♪

44
00:03:53,450 --> 00:03:55,120
Our current students

45
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:56,220
are in their senior year.

46
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:59,320
♪ On repeat, the song
tells the secret I can't speak ♪

47
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:58,190
Even though they're in the middle of
the final push,

48
00:03:58,190 --> 00:03:59,750
the overall study atmosphere

49
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:00,980
♪ The smile at the corner of your lips ♪

50
00:03:59,930 --> 00:04:00,760
-is very good.
-Hello, teachers!

51
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:01,630
Hello, hello.

52
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:02,950
It's just that

53
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:04,750
during the breaks,

54
00:04:05,070 --> 00:04:06,330
things get a bit loose.

55
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:07,580
Bu Guo,

56
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:10,230
your observation is spot on.

57
00:04:10,790 --> 00:04:12,660
I've noticed that too.

58
00:04:13,140 --> 00:04:14,980
Our college admission rate
has declined a bit

59
00:04:14,980 --> 00:04:16,339
over the past couple of years.

60
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:16,990
This year,

61
00:04:17,339 --> 00:04:18,940
we need to tighten things up.

62
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:19,959
Let's go.

63
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:26,230
[Bulletin Board]

64
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:26,220
Excuse me, excuse me.

65
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:28,260
Thank you, thank you.

66
00:04:31,210 --> 00:04:32,950
[School Celebration; Celebrating the
75th Anniversary of Qingmu High School]

67
00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:33,510
Isn't this the school's

68
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:35,040
annual grand celebration?

69
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:37,340
It's our last year at school.

70
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:38,870
Let's join together, okay?

71
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:40,820
Ning,

72
00:04:41,140 --> 00:04:41,990
let's do a double cello performance.

73
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:42,780
What do you think?

74
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:43,580
Let's do it?

75
00:04:44,260 --> 00:04:45,460
We haven't performed in ages.

76
00:04:45,460 --> 00:04:47,120
We should show off our skills.

77
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:47,950
Take a look.

78
00:04:47,690 --> 00:04:49,090
[Selection List for the Experimental Class
of Qingmu High School]

79
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:49,990
This experimental class

80
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:51,900
is a pilot program for our school.

81
00:04:50,340 --> 00:04:51,850
[Selection List for the Experimental Class
of Qingmu High School]

82
00:04:51,900 --> 00:04:53,460
We will select the top 30 students

83
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,700
in the grade,

84
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:57,140
who will be taught by a team of

85
00:04:57,140 --> 00:04:58,460
senior teachers and subject experts

86
00:04:58,460 --> 00:04:59,380
for one month.

87
00:05:00,140 --> 00:05:01,670
But our ultimate goal

88
00:05:01,670 --> 00:05:03,460
is to provide all students

89
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:05,410
with a more focused

90
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:07,990
and efficient learning environment.

91
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:10,430
I'll leave it to you.

92
00:05:10,430 --> 00:05:11,160
Director Hu!

93
00:05:12,260 --> 00:05:13,320
About Tong Xiaole.

94
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:14,990
You know

95
00:05:14,990 --> 00:05:15,580
his grades,

96
00:05:15,580 --> 00:05:16,670
but I've been

97
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:19,310
teaching him since his first year.

98
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:20,630
His personality

99
00:05:21,220 --> 00:05:22,070
is a bit...

100
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:24,460
a bit rebellious.

101
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:25,460
So I'm worried

102
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:26,750
he might

103
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:28,430
struggle with a new teacher,

104
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:30,190
and his grades might suffer.

105
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:31,050
How about this?

106
00:05:32,140 --> 00:05:34,140
I promise you—

107
00:05:34,340 --> 00:05:35,020
if

108
00:05:35,550 --> 00:05:37,080
you let him stay in my class,

109
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:38,220
I guarantee his grades

110
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:41,110
will remain stable
until the college entrance exam.

111
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:41,700
Mr. Bu,

112
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:43,920
I understand how you feel.

113
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:45,190
But the teachers

114
00:05:45,190 --> 00:05:47,020
for our experimental class are

115
00:05:47,020 --> 00:05:49,420
all specially certified senior teachers.

116
00:05:49,460 --> 00:05:51,590
They're certainly more experienced.

117
00:05:52,110 --> 00:05:52,909
It'll be fine.

118
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:54,700
Don't worry.

119
00:05:55,340 --> 00:05:56,700
Think it over.

120
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:02,680
Everyone, stop what you're doing.

121
00:06:09,820 --> 00:06:10,950
Starting tomorrow,

122
00:06:12,260 --> 00:06:13,720
all senior-year students

123
00:06:14,550 --> 00:06:16,020
must arrive before 6 a.m.

124
00:06:16,020 --> 00:06:17,420
for morning self-study.

125
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:18,780
Six a.m.?

126
00:06:19,340 --> 00:06:21,460
And all extracurricular club activities

127
00:06:21,460 --> 00:06:23,920
for senior-year students will be canceled.

128
00:06:24,670 --> 00:06:25,820
Ning, what about our...

129
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:27,260
All students will

130
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:31,260
return to school for review sessions
after school and on weekends.

131
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:32,340
No one

132
00:06:32,580 --> 00:06:35,670
will be permitted to take leave
under any circumstances.

133
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:36,700
We can't even take leave?

134
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:38,190
What if we get sick?

135
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:39,990
Quiet.

136
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:42,340
The following students, please stand up

137
00:06:42,340 --> 00:06:43,600
when I call your names:

138
00:06:44,510 --> 00:06:45,220
Luo Ningzi,

139
00:06:48,780 --> 00:06:49,670
Tong Xiaole,

140
00:06:54,510 --> 00:06:55,370
Chen Guoqiang,

141
00:06:57,110 --> 00:06:57,900
Wei Hu,

142
00:06:59,310 --> 00:07:00,190
and Chen Chen.

143
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:03,140
You...

144
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:05,820
will be assigned to the Experimental Class

145
00:07:05,820 --> 00:07:06,950
to study for a month.

146
00:07:07,340 --> 00:07:08,780
The Experimental Class?

147
00:07:08,990 --> 00:07:09,900
Mr. Bu,

148
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,020
why are we being split into
different classes?

149
00:07:11,020 --> 00:07:12,110
Shouldn't you discuss

150
00:07:12,110 --> 00:07:13,340
something like this with us first?

151
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:14,140
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

152
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:15,220
This isn't fair at all,

153
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:15,990
Mr. Bu!

154
00:07:16,220 --> 00:07:17,220
It's unfair!

155
00:07:18,110 --> 00:07:18,990
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

156
00:07:19,220 --> 00:07:20,020
Quiet!

157
00:07:21,620 --> 00:07:23,280
The school made this decision

158
00:07:23,460 --> 00:07:24,580
to help you

159
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:27,230
give it your all in the final push

160
00:07:27,340 --> 00:07:29,270
toward the college entrance exam.

161
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,960
And we also hope that you'll maintain

162
00:07:32,460 --> 00:07:34,820
an appropriate distance
in your interactions

163
00:07:34,820 --> 00:07:36,140
with students of the opposite sex.

164
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:38,580
There's nothing going on between us,
so what distance are you talking about?

165
00:07:38,580 --> 00:07:39,700
Crazy.

166
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:48,780
Yi Lan!

167
00:07:50,020 --> 00:07:51,140
What took you so long?

168
00:07:51,140 --> 00:07:52,670
Have you been waiting long?

169
00:07:54,190 --> 00:07:55,260
I won't hold you up.

170
00:07:55,260 --> 00:07:56,190
You two in front,

171
00:07:56,780 --> 00:07:57,780
stop right there!

172
00:07:57,780 --> 00:07:58,380
Come here!

173
00:07:59,230 --> 00:08:00,580
Don't you know boys and girls

174
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:01,980
can't share an umbrella?

175
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:03,280
Are you two dating?

176
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:05,720
Which class are you in?

177
00:08:06,140 --> 00:08:08,700
School rules don't allow boys and girls to
share an umbrella!

178
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:09,870
Come on! Come here.

179
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:11,960
Remember, from now on,

180
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:13,070
you can't share an umbrella.

181
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:14,270
What should we do now?

182
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:15,260
Let's go.

183
00:08:15,380 --> 00:08:15,990
Let's go!

184
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:17,460
Remember this.

185
00:08:27,110 --> 00:08:29,140
Why did you snatch my umbrella?

186
00:08:29,340 --> 00:08:30,550
My hair is all wet!

187
00:08:31,330 --> 00:08:31,810
Shan...

188
00:08:41,669 --> 00:08:42,950
Shan!

189
00:08:43,010 --> 00:08:45,930
-Shan! Shan!
-Shan!

190
00:08:45,950 --> 00:08:47,210
-Where are you?
-Shan?

191
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:48,950
There's a towel in the cabinet.

192
00:08:48,950 --> 00:08:49,810
Help yourself.

193
00:08:50,220 --> 00:08:50,980
Got it.

194
00:08:58,860 --> 00:09:00,790
When did they leave the money here?

195
00:09:13,100 --> 00:09:13,860
You actually

196
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:15,520
don't look half bad like this.

197
00:09:18,820 --> 00:09:19,500
Dry off quickly.

198
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,560
Don't catch a cold.

199
00:09:30,220 --> 00:09:31,310
Why are your exam papers

200
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:32,620
different from ours?

201
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,700
It's just different classes—

202
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:37,230
is there really a need
for unequal treatment?

203
00:09:38,070 --> 00:09:39,270
Then you finish them.

204
00:09:42,620 --> 00:09:43,270
No need.

205
00:09:50,430 --> 00:09:53,430
Did they call you in
to discuss college applications?

206
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:56,720
Hailan University...

207
00:09:57,430 --> 00:09:58,890
Photography Department.

208
00:09:59,950 --> 00:10:00,950
Photography Department?

209
00:10:00,950 --> 00:10:01,880
You've decided?

210
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:06,980
But why Hailan University?

211
00:10:06,980 --> 00:10:07,860
With your grades,

212
00:10:07,860 --> 00:10:10,270
shouldn't you be aiming for
a more competitive school?

213
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:11,870
Because you're going there.

214
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:13,900
What does that have to do with me?

215
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:16,430
I'm worried that

216
00:10:16,430 --> 00:10:17,820
after you go to Hailan University,

217
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:19,460
you'll get pushed around.

218
00:10:19,460 --> 00:10:20,150
And without me to protect you,

219
00:10:20,150 --> 00:10:21,080
what will you do?

220
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:22,630
Who are you looking down on?

221
00:10:25,820 --> 00:10:26,740
So impressive.

222
00:10:27,430 --> 00:10:28,190
You bet.

223
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:32,030
Let me show you something.

224
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:32,500
What?

225
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:36,150
Of course, it's the photo

226
00:10:36,150 --> 00:10:38,340
I took specifically of you that day,

227
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:40,580
and I developed it specifically...

228
00:10:41,220 --> 00:10:42,460
just to give to you.

229
00:10:42,820 --> 00:10:44,350
Handsome, don't you think?

230
00:10:48,460 --> 00:10:49,310
Smile.

231
00:11:04,950 --> 00:11:06,410
You're only noticing now?

232
00:11:07,070 --> 00:11:09,860
You've only captured
a fraction of my charm.

233
00:11:09,950 --> 00:11:11,390
I-I-It's not bad.

234
00:11:16,620 --> 00:11:17,500
So handsome.

235
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:22,310
Actually, I...

236
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:25,790
I know that day

237
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:26,980
you were trying to help me

238
00:11:26,980 --> 00:11:28,820
be firmer about my photography dream,

239
00:11:28,820 --> 00:11:30,480
so you invited everyone over.

240
00:11:30,980 --> 00:11:31,740
Thank you.

241
00:11:34,190 --> 00:11:35,740
No need to thank me!

242
00:11:35,950 --> 00:11:37,670
We're friends!

243
00:11:38,460 --> 00:11:39,840
I've always known about

244
00:11:39,980 --> 00:11:41,510
your dream of photography,

245
00:11:41,580 --> 00:11:44,100
so of course, I'd go all out for you.

246
00:11:48,820 --> 00:11:49,740
It's my dream.

247
00:11:49,740 --> 00:11:51,070
Why are you so happy?

248
00:11:51,620 --> 00:11:52,550
Of course.

249
00:11:52,950 --> 00:11:55,680
You were so indecisive
about choosing a major...

250
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:04,270
[Solution]

251
00:12:44,220 --> 00:12:44,670
Hurry up,

252
00:12:44,670 --> 00:12:45,800
we're gonna be late!

253
00:12:47,460 --> 00:12:49,700
Why don't you go by yourself today?

254
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:50,980
I'm not going.

255
00:12:51,070 --> 00:12:51,870
What's wrong?

256
00:12:52,190 --> 00:12:53,340
Are you not feeling well?

257
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:55,070
Did you catch a cold yesterday?

258
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:57,550
You're fine.

259
00:13:00,580 --> 00:13:01,820
I didn't finish my homework.

260
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:02,980
Mr. Bu said anyone who doesn't finish it

261
00:13:02,980 --> 00:13:04,100
has to run 5,000 meters as punishment.

262
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:06,160
I'll be half dead after running that.

263
00:13:06,340 --> 00:13:07,540
I'm really not going.

264
00:13:10,070 --> 00:13:10,820
Turn around.

265
00:13:15,580 --> 00:13:16,620
Will you be late?

266
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:17,700
Do you want to go ahead?

267
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:18,220
No.

268
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,460
Then write faster.

269
00:13:20,980 --> 00:13:22,190
Make it look like I wrote it!

270
00:13:22,190 --> 00:13:22,980
Shut up.

271
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:25,270
Keep talking, and we really will be late.

272
00:13:25,270 --> 00:13:26,340
Don't get them all correct...

273
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:26,820
Done.

274
00:13:28,980 --> 00:13:29,510
Let's go.

275
00:13:30,820 --> 00:13:32,150
You're amazing!

276
00:13:33,220 --> 00:13:34,100
Get on the bike, hurry.

277
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:34,950
Or we'll really be late.

278
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:36,350
You really are a prodigy.

279
00:13:38,980 --> 00:13:39,740
Which class are you in?

280
00:13:39,740 --> 00:13:40,340
Class 9.

281
00:13:40,430 --> 00:13:42,460
Don't you know
badminton rackets aren't allowed?

282
00:13:42,460 --> 00:13:43,990
This isn't allowed either.

283
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:49,000
Which class?

284
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:49,950
Experimental Class.

285
00:13:49,950 --> 00:13:51,030
Experimental Class?

286
00:13:51,030 --> 00:13:51,580
Go ahead.

287
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:53,700
Thank you for your hard work.

288
00:13:54,220 --> 00:13:54,950
Which class?

289
00:13:55,070 --> 00:13:57,100
-Class 9.
-Who told you that you could eat?

290
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:57,980
Where's your phone?

291
00:13:57,980 --> 00:13:58,500
Didn't bring it.

292
00:13:58,500 --> 00:13:59,340
I didn't bring it.

293
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:01,820
Basketballs aren't allowed either,
you know that?

294
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:02,550
Hand it over.

295
00:14:03,820 --> 00:14:04,740
We used to be allowed to bring them,

296
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:05,850
and now we're not?

297
00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:08,030
Forget it.

298
00:14:08,460 --> 00:14:09,340
Students,

299
00:14:09,820 --> 00:14:12,020
what I'm about to say is very important.

300
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:12,820
We've

301
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:14,980
figured out 80% of the questions
that are likely

302
00:14:14,980 --> 00:14:16,180
to appear on the exam.

303
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:16,980
Write

304
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:18,820
them down now, alright?

305
00:14:32,490 --> 00:14:37,700
[Pass through a straight line;
A point not on the line]

306
00:14:35,740 --> 00:14:36,700
Look at your textbooks.

307
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:38,360
The blackboard is over there.

308
00:14:41,070 --> 00:14:42,740
Male and female students are forbidden...

309
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:44,200
from walking side by side.

310
00:14:46,050 --> 00:14:47,460
No basketball?

311
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:47,990
[Qingmu High School
Evening Self-Study Regulations (2022)]

312
00:14:48,310 --> 00:14:49,770
No strolling on the track?

313
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:54,910
Why are there so many stupid rules?

314
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:57,170
[Qingmu High School
Evening Self-Study Regulations (2022)]

315
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:56,780
Especially this one—

316
00:14:56,820 --> 00:14:58,670
no food allowed in school.

317
00:14:57,190 --> 00:14:58,580
[Qingmu High School
Evening Self-Study Regulations (2022)]

318
00:14:58,950 --> 00:14:59,620
I can't believe it.

319
00:14:59,620 --> 00:15:01,460
I'm starving every day.

320
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:03,790
Is there such a rule?

321
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:09,230
You guys in the Experimental Class
don't have that rule?

322
00:15:09,620 --> 00:15:10,340
No.

323
00:15:11,740 --> 00:15:12,430
I want one too.

324
00:15:12,430 --> 00:15:13,550
It's unfair.

325
00:15:13,850 --> 00:15:16,510
This is clearly targeting
our regular classes.

326
00:15:21,580 --> 00:15:22,150
Let's go.

327
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:24,790
Go. Go.

328
00:15:50,460 --> 00:15:51,460
Mr. Bu, my stomach hurts.

329
00:15:51,460 --> 00:15:52,990
I need to go to the bathroom.

330
00:15:53,340 --> 00:15:54,000
Go quickly.

331
00:16:08,460 --> 00:16:10,070
Mr. Bu, she has a headache.

332
00:16:15,580 --> 00:16:18,500
Mr. Bu, I want to go back early

333
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,910
and rest a bit.

334
00:16:24,910 --> 00:16:27,110
Then just sleep on your desk for a while.

335
00:16:28,190 --> 00:16:28,860
You too.

336
00:16:30,620 --> 00:16:31,340
Hurry.

337
00:16:35,790 --> 00:16:36,520
Keep it down.

338
00:16:48,070 --> 00:16:48,580
Mr. Bu.

339
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:00,580
Is the bubble tea here?

340
00:17:00,580 --> 00:17:01,710
It's here. Let's go.

341
00:17:18,630 --> 00:17:19,910
Does everyone have one?

342
00:17:19,910 --> 00:17:21,630
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

343
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:23,329
[Experimental Class]

344
00:17:39,780 --> 00:17:41,430
As expected of the Experimental Class—

345
00:17:41,430 --> 00:17:42,630
look at their energy.

346
00:17:42,740 --> 00:17:44,400
No one even dares to slack off.

347
00:17:44,910 --> 00:17:46,740
And they each have a cup of bubble tea,

348
00:17:46,740 --> 00:17:48,140
given out by the teacher.

349
00:17:52,980 --> 00:17:55,150
Why don't they have all those rules?

350
00:17:56,630 --> 00:17:58,760
Aren't we being treated differently?

351
00:17:59,730 --> 00:18:00,580
Of course.

352
00:18:01,190 --> 00:18:03,540
The school favors these top students.

353
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:06,190
We just get spoon-fed education,

354
00:18:06,260 --> 00:18:09,020
while they enjoy VIP treatment.

355
00:18:09,070 --> 00:18:10,910
Top students, top students,

356
00:18:11,260 --> 00:18:12,190
